    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Is Monte Carlo Tree Search?"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) is a decision-time planning algorithm that builds a search tree incrementally using statistical sampling. Instead of exhaustively exploring all possible futures, MCTS repeatedly runs four phases \u2014 "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Selection, Expansion, Simulation, Backpropagation"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " \u2014 to focus computation on the most promising branches. It was the algorithm behind AlphaGo and is directly applicable to LLM agent planning."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "MCTS four phases: Selection (UCB traversal), Expansion (add new node), Simulation (random rollout to terminal), Backpropagation (update visit counts and scores up the tree)",
          "title": "MCTS four phases: select, expand, simulate, backpropagate"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "MCTS is the algorithm of choice when: (1) the branching factor is high so exhaustive search is infeasible, (2) a fast simulation (rollout) function is available, and (3) the search budget is time-bounded rather than exhaustive."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Node Structure and UCB"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each node stores the state it represents, the action that led to it, visit count, and accumulated simulation score. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Upper Confidence Bound (UCB)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " formula balances "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "exploitation"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (high Q nodes) vs "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "exploration"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (less-visited nodes):"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import math\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass MCTSNode:\n    state: object          # any hashable representation of the current state\n    parent: Optional[\"MCTSNode\"] = None\n    action: Optional[str]  = None   # action that led to this state\n    children: list[\"MCTSNode\"] = field(default_factory=list)\n    visits: int   = 0\n    value:  float = 0.0   # accumulated simulation scores\n\n    @property\n    def q(self) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Average value (exploitation term).\"\"\"\n        return self.value / self.visits if self.visits > 0 else 0.0\n\n    def ucb(self, c: float = 1.414) -> float:\n        \"\"\"Upper Confidence Bound for Trees.\n\n        c=sqrt(2) balances exploration vs exploitation.\n        Returns infinity for unvisited nodes (guarantees they are tried).\n        \"\"\"\n        if self.visits == 0:\n            return float(\"inf\")\n        parent_visits = self.parent.visits if self.parent else self.visits\n        return self.q + c * math.sqrt(math.log(parent_visits) / self.visits)\n\n    def best_child(self, c: float = 1.414) -> \"MCTSNode\":\n        return max(self.children, key=lambda n: n.ucb(c))"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The exploration constant "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "c = sqrt(2)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the standard choice derived from theory. In practice, tuning "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "c"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for the specific domain often improves results: higher "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "c"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " explores more; lower "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "c"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " exploits more."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Four Phases"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def selection(node: MCTSNode) -> MCTSNode:\n    \"\"\"Traverse the tree using UCB until a leaf node is reached.\"\"\"\n    while node.children:                   # while fully expanded\n        node = node.best_child()        # pick child with highest UCB\n    return node\n\ndef expansion(\n    node: MCTSNode,\n    get_actions: callable,\n    apply_action: callable,\n) -> MCTSNode:\n    \"\"\"Add one new child to the node (one untried action).\"\"\"\n    tried_actions = {c.action for c in node.children}\n    untried = [a for a in get_actions(node.state) if a not in tried_actions]\n    if not untried:\n        return node  # fully expanded \u2014 return node for simulation\n    action = untried[0]  # pick first untried; random is also common\n    new_state = apply_action(node.state, action)\n    child = MCTSNode(state=new_state, parent=node, action=action)\n    node.children.append(child)\n    return child\n\ndef simulation(node: MCTSNode, rollout: callable) -> float:\n    \"\"\"Simulate to a terminal state and return a score in [0, 1].\"\"\"\n    return rollout(node.state)  # random or heuristic policy\n\ndef backpropagation(node: MCTSNode, score: float) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Update visit counts and values from node to root.\"\"\"\n    while node is not None:\n        node.visits += 1\n        node.value  += score\n        node = node.parent"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Selection:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " descends the tree using UCB until a node with untried actions (a leaf) is found. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Expansion:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " adds one new child for an untried action. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Simulation:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " a rollout policy (random or heuristic) plays out from the new node to a terminal state and returns a score. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Backpropagation:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " the score propagates up the tree, incrementing visit counts and adding to accumulated values."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Main Loop"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The four phases combine into a straightforward loop. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "most-visited"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " child (not highest Q) is returned as the best action \u2014 most-visited is more robust to outlier high-score nodes:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def mcts(\n    root_state: object,\n    get_actions: callable,\n    apply_action: callable,\n    rollout: callable,\n    n_iterations: int = 1000,\n    c: float = 1.414,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Run MCTS for n_iterations and return the best action from root.\n\n    get_actions(state) -> list[action]\n    apply_action(state, action) -> new_state\n    rollout(state) -> float in [0, 1]\n    \"\"\"\n    root = MCTSNode(state=root_state)\n\n    for _ in range(n_iterations):\n        # 1. Selection\n        leaf = selection(root)\n        # 2. Expansion (if not terminal)\n        if get_actions(leaf.state):\n            leaf = expansion(leaf, get_actions, apply_action)\n        # 3. Simulation\n        score = simulation(leaf, rollout)\n        # 4. Backpropagation\n        backpropagation(leaf, score)\n\n    # Return the most-visited child action (robust, not highest Q)\n    best = max(root.children, key=lambda n: n.visits)\n    return best.action"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM as Action Generator and Rollout"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For open-ended planning tasks, the LLM replaces the symbolic action generator and rollout function. The action generator proposes candidate next steps; the rollout function scores the current plan path directly, without simulation to a terminal state:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM_ROLLOUT_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nYou are evaluating a partial plan for a goal.\nScore how likely this plan path is to succeed in achieving the goal.\n\nGoal: {goal}\nPlan so far: {actions_taken}\nCurrent state: {state}\n\nScore on a scale of 0.0 (certain failure) to 1.0 (certain success).\nReturn JSON: {{\"score\": 0.0-1.0, \"reasoning\": \"<one sentence>\"}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef llm_rollout(goal: str) -> callable:\n    \"\"\"Returns a rollout function that uses the LLM to score plan states.\"\"\"\n    def rollout(state: dict) -> float:\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n            max_tokens=256,\n            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": LLM_ROLLOUT_PROMPT.format(\n                goal=goal,\n                actions_taken=state.get(\"actions\", []),\n                state=state.get(\"facts\", {}),\n            )}],\n        )\n        data = json.loads(response.content[0].text)\n        return float(data[\"score\"])\n    return rollout\n\nLLM_ACTIONS_PROMPT = \"\"\"\nGiven the current state and goal, list the 3-5 most promising next actions.\nGoal: {goal}\nCurrent state: {state}\nReturn JSON: {{\"actions\": [\"action1\", \"action2\", ...]}}\n\"\"\"\n\ndef llm_get_actions(goal: str) -> callable:\n    def get_actions(state: dict) -> list[str]:\n        if state.get(\"terminal\"):\n            return []\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n            max_tokens=256,\n            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": LLM_ACTIONS_PROMPT.format(\n                goal=goal,\n                state=state,\n            )}],\n        )\n        return json.loads(response.content[0].text)[\"actions\"]\n    return get_actions"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Cost note:"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " using the LLM as rollout is expensive \u2014 every MCTS iteration makes a model call. Keep "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "n_iterations"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " low (20\u201350) when using LLM rollouts, and use a fast cheap model. For symbolic domains, 1000+ iterations are practical."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Full LLM-Backed MCTS Planning"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Combining LLM action generation and evaluation with the MCTS loop:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def mcts_plan(\n    goal: str,\n    initial_state: dict,\n    n_iterations: int = 50,   # keep low when LLM is the rollout (expensive)\n) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"MCTS planning loop using LLM for action generation and evaluation.\n\n    Returns the sequence of actions on the best path found.\n    \"\"\"\n    get_actions = llm_get_actions(goal)\n    rollout     = llm_rollout(goal)\n\n    def apply_action(state: dict, action: str) -> dict:\n        new_actions = state.get(\"actions\", []) + [action]\n        # Mark terminal if we have 5+ actions (depth limit)\n        terminal = len(new_actions) >= 5\n        return {\"actions\": new_actions, \"terminal\": terminal, \"facts\": state.get(\"facts\", {})}\n\n    root = MCTSNode(state=initial_state)\n    for _ in range(n_iterations):\n        leaf = selection(root)\n        if get_actions(leaf.state):\n            leaf = expansion(leaf, get_actions, apply_action)\n        score = simulation(leaf, rollout)\n        backpropagation(leaf, score)\n\n    # Trace the best path (most-visited at each level)\n    path = []\n    node = root\n    while node.children:\n        node = max(node.children, key=lambda n: n.visits)\n        if node.action:\n            path.append(node.action)\n    return path\n\n# Example:\n# plan = mcts_plan(\n#     goal=\"Research and write a comparison of three Python HTTP libraries\",\n#     initial_state={\"actions\": [], \"terminal\": False, \"facts\": {}},\n#     n_iterations=30,\n# )"
          }
        ]
      },
